Potent, but not devastating. Nice, mellow, balanced high that leans sativa in its effects. Buzzy but clear cerebral effects kick in first, followed by a buttery-smooth body buzz. It got rid of my nasty headache, and replaced it with a happy, floaty, mellow high that lasted almost 2 hours. JQ Has a nice, gradual come-down and doesn't leave you feeling fatigued like some strains can. Puts you in the zone for watching sports or movies, as you can focus—and maintain focus—on a narrative and comprehend it.  Also good for making housework not feel so much like drudgery. I imagine it would also be great campfire weed. (Not too trippy, not too chatty: great story-telling weed.) Didn't give me the munchies, but beer and wine are quite good with it. Pretty standard dry mouth and dry eye effects, especially on the back end. I'd buy it again.

I just tried this strain for the very first time and I must say, this is my favorite so far! First off, it has a pretty unique look. The buds appear over dried, but have the most vivid orange hairs I have ever seen! It is a very sight. The buds were also full and fluffy. Second, the thing that impressed me the most was that it actually smelled just like a fresh tangerine! EXACTLY like a fresh tangerine! I have never had a strain that smelled so much like the name! The smoke tasted great! I recognized more of a tangerine essence in the smell rather than the taste, but it still tasted great, nonetheless. As the description says on this bio, it does start off as a social smoke where you can stay focused and carry on a conversation. I'm not feeling so much energetic (as I've had a long day), but I can definitely see it as such. However, too much can leave you with couch lock. That's probably the second v reason why I make this strain my favorite. You can almost control your high with this one. I'd say it's comparable to Camel crush cigarettes in that you can switch from one type of effect to another...but I highly prefer Tangerine Dream over a cigarette any day! All in all, I strongly recommend this strain. Pleasing to the eyes, nose, and taste buds while still delivering a versatile smoke. If you find Tangerine Dream, I strongly suggest you try it. You definitely will not regret it. Happy smoking ;)

God’s Gift consistently performs well (at least 18-22% THC) when lab-tested and has a delicious berry flavor patients seem to love. Because of this, God’s Gift would most-likely be a good option for patients looking for a significant boost in appetite as well as a natural stress/pain reliever.
God’s Gift has a strong berry aroma and taste similar to Granddaddy Purple but with more fresh citrus and lemon after-tones. Visually, the God’s Gift strain should be extremely purple, dense, and covered in sparkling white crystals. Anything other than that would leave me disappointed after so I’ve been blessed with so many good batches of God’s Gift.
The effects are exactly as you’d expect from a heavy Indica-dominant hybrid: instant, full-bodied, and tiring. The God’d Gift strain seems to leave you in a peaceful daze that just creeps and creeps until you start yawning and looking for somewhere to lay down and get comfortable. This is why I try to only medicate with the God’s Gift strain late at night.

Northern Lights review!

Appearance 
This was a beautiful sample to look at, both up-close and from afar. The sample i received was in the form of one large nug that had an artful trim, showcasing all the “inner-workings” of the nug but still leaving a perfect amount of leaf matter behind to look natural. The coloration was very light overall, with crispy greens and almost golden-colored pistils in places. this sample, it was a simply beautiful and well cared-for example of an Indica structured strain.

Flavor 
Lightly sweet and citrusy on the inhale, more piney and musky on the exhale, this strain definitely tasted much like it smelled, though less pungent overall. The smoke and flavor had a smooth quality that is described as “buttery”, but it also had elements of expansion that could cause some coughing on larger hits. The smooth experience with solid flavor preservation (4-5 hits) finished out with a very light gray and white ash, showing a very good flush

personal opinion ONLY) Mood elevation, ocular effects, muscle relaxation, moderate pain relief, heavily sedative,

This is excellent for those seeking an energetic, crystal-clear high.  This made me incredibly focused, yet quieted my busy mind -- I have ADD and this works wonders for focus and concentration.  I also felt happy and uplifted, and my busy brain quieted down.  No bad effects for me except a little dry mouth.  Would be great for morning/daytime use, at night it would probably keep you awake.  Recommended for working, studying, being active, chatting with friends.  Doesn't produce as much of a euphoria for me, more of a feeling of well-being and focused energy, with mild body effects.  Perfect for depression, lethargy, ADD/ADHD.  A+ for morning/daytime use.

My wife has fibromyalgia and prescription medication often helps, but sometimes doesn't really -- depending on the type of pain and location in her body.  Blue Dream is perfect for her joint pain and erases it for hours, as well as being good for muscle spasms and menstrual cramps.  Unlike other hybrids, this isn't so Indica-heavy that it knocks you out.  Instead you're very, very relaxed but awake.  Minor "couch lock" and slightly increased hunger, but not much.  This is one of the best strains we've ever tried for pain management as well as calming mood, with the least side effects.  Outstanding unless you need something for morning use -- I wouldn't recommend then.

The perfect balance of effects: incredibly relaxing, yet uplifting and euphoric.  Would be my #1 choice for reducing stress and anxiety/PTSD.  Does produce some "couch lock" ... but has a wonderful, warm body effect that lasts for hours.  Makes me happy and a little giggly but mostly just calm, relaxed, and I slept great afterwards.  Would highly recommend for those who don't like straight Indica but want some of the Indica effects: you get body effects but also the more sativa-like uplifting and mood elevation.  Only time I wouldn't recommend would be for morning use, this is more of a late afternoon/evening strain.  There's a reason this is a classic strain that is well-loved by many.  If you are looking for physical and mental relaxation and mood elevation with no paranoia, you can't go wrong with this one!
***update:  Some Dutch Treat has more Sativa characteristics than others, this particular batch I had was more on the Indica side -- got from Pharmaseed.  A later batch from Safe Access was much more Sativa-dominant and had less of the sleepy, body relaxation effects (but was still great!)

Since using marijuana medically, this was the first strain I tried. I eat it, it is a dark thick tar-like substance in a syringe. I take about 1/4 - 1/2 size of a grain of rice. It takes about an hour to take effect. When it does, I am couch locked, giggly, definitely feel high, and I care a lot less about my pain. Sometimes it makes me feel more tense, or maybe sort of highlights the tension in my neck and shoulders, where I tend to carry my stress. 

However, if I take more than my usual dose, which I did the other day - it wasn't doing it for me, the pain was still intense, so I took another dose - I ought to have only taken a tiny bit more - but I did another 1/4 - 1/2 grain of rice size bit - it was NOT good. I became overly emotional, my anxiety shot through the roof, I was weepy and paranoid and my thoughts spiraled into super negativity land. DARK thoughts. The only way I made it go away was to sleep it off - which only took a couple of hours but man alive, I have to be really careful with this strain, as I seem to be very sensitive to high CBD strains in that way. 

I so very much wanted to find a strain with less of the high and more of the pain relief, but this one wasn't it. I still use it occasionally when there isn't anything else available, but this one it too unpredictable for me. If I have something else available, chances are I will use that instead. And eating it can be unpredictable anyway - I would be very curious to try vaping this one to see if it is different in flower form.

I actually quite liked Black Cherry Soda at first. It was recommended to me to help me sleep and to calm my brain at night (to help me sleep). But I've actually found I prefer it as a daytime strain.  Although it isn't the most active of feelings, I am able to get tasks accomplished while using it, like chores, banking online, and my crafts. I wouldn't say I feel clear- headed, but I feel lucid enough to communicate effectively and not come off as "stoned" though I can't say I don't feel high.  It does relax me, make my pain much less significant - like I just pay less attention to it but also I seem to get some relief - a little anyway. 

But after using it awhile, in liquid pen vape form, I noticed I began to get headaches whenever I would use it. And I think that is the delivery system and not the strain itself. It started after I used it for a full day rather than just once, and it happened every time I'd use it. So I went down to once a day again, and it continued, even continuing to give me a headache the day after I had used it. I know it was this because I am damn familiar with my own body and all the different kinds of pain I experience, and this was a new one. I don't even know how to explain it. So I stopped, went to my edibles, no headache. I am positive it is the glycerin medium used in making the liquid and not the strain itself. I'm going to test my theory by getting a gram of BCS flower to dry vape or smoke. I'll report back if that also gives me a headache or not.

While I've experienced only a handful of strains in my time, SFV is by far my favorite. Even before vaping it, the smell of it is incredible. The high, on the other hand, is absolutely incredible. My first time vaping it, I remember thinking that it felt like "weed 2.0." I usually get some paranoia and a good deal of self-consciousness while high, but all that is gone with this strain. It's just solid relaxation and euphoria. Nice dark flavorful Gorilla Glue Oil. I'm dabbing some on a sore inside a nostril, so the whole world smells sweet & dank. This is a subtle Gorilla. Maybe it's Gorilla Glue #6 ;-). It's serious medicine, I don't think it's for the get-fucked-up crowd :  because the effect is so specific. I don't really notice the (78%) THC so much. It's rather masked or antagonized by other components. So there's no squirrel cage shutter-flutter, no anxieties, no confusion, and some might say "no high". For social anxiety, it would be a good choice. It's balanced, more on the Indica side -- that unquestionably comes through with a good body melt, and I can believe the reports of couch lock w/ large amounts. Thing is, I wouldn't dream of wasting it that way.

In small amounts it's a blessing for those living with pain. I know pain, and I know remedies. This is the most atypical cannabis I've ever sampled, because it almost feels like puffs of ope, but with a somehow smarter, more benign analgesia than w/ Rx analgesics. Not a simple thing. But it works calm and measured, positive mood, not fake-euphoric, and with significant pain relief, not limited to the lower spine/legs/back. Pretty long lasting. After a while I notice a subtle secondary boost, sensory, and very mild "psychedelic" effects come in. Not a sleepy effect, yet good to fall asleep on. I haven't fully figured it out; it's intriguing. 

On the negatives, well, De Quincy would say who cares, but it's clearly not a party strain. I'd add that it's not as clear-headed as e.g. my favorite Diesels. It lasts, but as it decays I get a smidge fuzzy and sleepy, with a touch of headache, eyes a bit redder than I'd have guessed (so it's relaxing blood vessels). 

Focus? With the Gorilla, I can focus on tasks, get a little side-tracked, not feeling lightning bright, but keep going. The unusual pain relief allows all sorts of miraculous tricks, like walking around without wincing, and fully enjoying exploring the planet. A good one to keep in a vape pen for as-needed relief.

I can see why many people would like it. It's strong, it's intoxicating, and offers a bit of everything, and could be funny in good company. It does a mostly sativa thing, unmitigated THC dominates, with scrambled thoughts, some body relax, some good mood, some sedation, some dreamy poof, some paranoid anxiety. Not for me. I would guess that different phenotypes of Blue Dream could be very different, so I wouldn't cross it off entirely. It's not on my Avoid At All Costs list, like Trainwreck, but if you prefer a more focused head, this one is likely too "recreational" for ya.

-----------INTRODUCTION---------
To start this off I'll say this strain is wonderous. So I hit up my dealer asking what he's got and he tells me he has Blue Dream. I quickly  text back that I'll take some but I say it in a way that'll make me seem like I haven't lost my cool. So  I get home from work and my grandma sends me to the store to grab some groceries. I say okay then immediately go upstairs to my room to grind up this beauty and stuff it into my acrylic bong. As I sat there demolishing the perfectly packed nugget of Blue Dream I couldn't help but notice the amount of crystals it had. Now along with my acrylic bong I have a matching acrylic grinder that does not have fancy chambers and luxuries of that nature. No, my single bottom-and-top-cap-with-teeth grinder doesn't collect keif. So I think to myself a little nug wouldn't hurt. I refrain from grinding and collect a small nug which I so carefully place on top of the screen in the bowl of the bong and I toke away. One smooth hit and I was able to fill the chamber of this 12" acrylic bong and take an additional hit from the smoke in the chamber. I grab my keys and I embark on an adventure.
--------THE STONED MAN---------
I really hope you guys get my Hobbit reference just then. Anyways, so I walk out to my truck and I feel the tingles happening behind my head, and I thought "nice cerebral buzz" and it was. I drive over to my local grocery store and i feel the effects intesify. The focus, the increased view of my peripheral vision, the energy coming from no where making my mind make decisions effectivly and quickly. I parked and walked inside, at this point my eyes are heavy (not from sleep). I pace myself looking at the different isles. I walk looking for a particular item and when i get to the isle it should be at, theres nothing there. I walk around the store twice looking for assistance only to come back to the isle i was at and asking an employee there. I ask a clerk where it would be and he takes me to an isle close by and hands me the item. I say thanks and walk away. Granted, this doesnt sound like much, but it took me about 20 minutes to ask someone for assistance, at one point i stood still staring at a girl because i thought she worked at the store but couldnt figure out, i later found out she did in fact work there. So i get one item and i go get the rest of the stuff. I continue admiring the store and i end up at the check out lane. I get checked out and the effects are now slowly wearing off. I go to by truck and the ride home is amazing. Looking at all the lights on houses was so invigorating.
------------THE END------------
Finally back home i walk in hand my grandma the groceries and she asked for her change. I gave her everything in my wallet (close to $150 and I walked away. Her change was only $8. I come back and I grab the money I count it and correct my error. And by now effects are at their faint, but euphoria was still present. 

----------THE VERDICT-----------

To the cognoscenti, the name says a lot. It's a Diesel with a purple Indica back. I found this in Eureka, I was driving through. The address and GPS took me to a shoe shop with a relatively surly occupant. I waited patiently as he whipped a customer into shape over the phone, laying down the law on shoeology. They sell serious footwear. Having driven in nano-clean from Canada, crossing dangerous regions like Montana and Idaho where they have firing squads for people like us, I was willing to go along with anyone's method. But I was trying to grasp the situation, imagining old Cerberus pulling a curtain aside, revealing rows of mason jars of medicinal buds in the closet, above the boots. He finally got off the phone and cracked his massive head towards me. I tried "collective" ... he gave me a chilling visual evaluation and said "I thought so. The pot shop. In the back". I asked why he "thought so", but he wasn't going there. It was clear he knew the drill. "Out back". 

I was happy to find the crew out back gentle and scattered. Lots of kids and a mother hen. They even had half-grams. I got several to try, including the dread Green Crack that they apologetically also called green something harmless. But one of my better purchases was a sun-grown and desiccated Purple Diesel. A Diesel - up, focused, energetic - with sedative and body melt notes. That's a complicated hybrid. Imagine a driving, four on the floor, synthy Electronic Dance Music - with a liquid fretless bass line. After the shoe-man, it was just the thing to get us back on the road. It's a composition I swore I'd be checking out again. I've encountered it since then as "Purple D", need to study it some more.

Lucid and awake yet dreamy, very distracted from what I was up to but still noticing peripheral ongoings.'Wavy' and 'psychedelic' are common words in this strain's comments for a reason- everything you look at is vivid, colorful and clear. 
Colors 'pop' a tad more than usual. 
It's also super easy to drift into your thoughts with Haze. The best advice I can extend, and the only thing that saved my lightweight ass from paranoia, was plenty of great music. Auditory attention is hugely expanded and uplifted with this strain, and your tunes will be tenfold as pleasing. 
Absolutely no paranoia in my trip, which is incredibly rare for me involving such an intense strain. 
For me, Haze is the perfect example of what the experience of 'weed' should be. 
Not tiring or scary, just impressive and interesting. 
Definitely recommend, but not to the first-timer as it can be overpowering at first.

Notable negative effects include: paranoia/anxiety-inducement, likely potential to be overwhelming for newbie cannabis users, decreased long-term focus

Good for days off; not good for whenever you are given certain amounts of responsibility (though, as I mentioned before, it is possible that I feel this way simply because I, personally, had felt overwhelmed and quite anxious while I was at work).

I ground up a decent-sized nug and filled the bowl. First hit was surprisingly harsh, so I choked pretty hard and didn't clear the bong or cash the bowl. I pulled and exhaled the stale smoke and re-lit the bowl. Smoother this time, maybe because I was expecting it. I waited about 4-5 minutes and deciding I wasn't feeling anything and packed another bowl. Full again, but I went it it a little more cautiously, inhaling more slowly, and it reduced the harshness and I didn't choke. After that large hit, I began to feel my eyelids relaxing and I knew the ride had begun. I remember why it's called "Headband", because of the feeling of something resting on the crown of your head. To me, it feels like a 3-pound donut that is pressing my skull, but not in a bad way, just like I need to keep my head up and balanced to keep it from falling off. Anyway, dry mouth came on pretty quickly, but not as bad as I get it from Girl Scout Cookies or some other Kush varieties. I always drink mango juice when I'm smoking, so I don't mind feeling thirsty. My lower-back pain went away pretty quickly, and all my joint pain melted after that. Not terribly couchlocked, but I definitely feel like staying in this chair for a bit. Definitely no munchies, although my stomach feels calmer than usual, which is nice. Everything is visually stimulating, especially bright colors. My third bowl has been 4 hits over about an hour, and I'm feeling great. Watching TV with my wife should always be this awesome. Finally, my eyes aren't really dry at all, whereas some strains leave me hitting the eyedrops right after exhaling.

I'm rating Headband as a 4 simply because of its heavy, thick, rough smoke. Everything else is great; pain relief, relaxation, de-stress/anxiety relief, and only minor dry mouth and eyes. If you mentally prepare to take long, slow rips, you'll be happy with Headband. 

Keep your head up straight or you'll drop the donut thingy!

I am writing this review post-high and after I've ran out so I'm just going to write about my remembered experience, which wasn't good the first time I used it and another time during the month that I had some.  Both times I did too much and experienced severe paranoia, my heart raced, and I could feel my muscles pulling.  Too much meaning 2-3 hits on the bong.  This strain is low in THC so I kept thinking I wasn't feeling anything so I took another hit.  Bad move.  I've learned the hard way not to judge my medicine dose by "how I feel" because I can't do that with low THC/High CBD strains.  Where the paranoia came from I don't know because I don't see it listed as one of the problems with this strain.  Which means it is affecting me differently than the national average.  I did find that if I just took 1 hit only and waited 1 1/2 to 2 hours between hits that I did not experience that paranoia.  Unfortunately I did not experience a lot of pain relief either.  It did help me to fall asleep though but some Sativas do me the same way and this is supposed to be an Indica dominant Hybrid.  I'm beginning to get concerned that my experiences with different strains do not coincide with the norm so I will not be able to use the charts to figure out what strains would be best for me.  It's just going to be trial and error, which could take me longer since I may not be able to use the advice of the internet web sites like Leafly which has compiled a great amount of information for us to use.  So my conclusion is this strain is pretty much useless to me if I only get pain relief when I use too much and get paranoia.  Not fun.

I strongly recommend this strain for anyone looking to get a great nights sleep, trying to relax after a hard days work, need to cure your headache/muscle/body pains(I only had minor ones at the time so for anything serious I can't say). I do not recommend smoking this strain in large amounts or for anyone trying to get a high to more enjoy various activities such as work or hanging out with friends(unless you are all just chillin out maxin relaxin all cool).

Tilray patient review:
Watermelon smell/flavour definitely there.
The euphoria in this strain is intense for an indica. It is uplifting and energizing. I don't feel sleepy and I can do a variety of activities and not feel couch locked. I prefer to use it during the day, not the evening.
I don't really notice the typical indica body effects until the euphoria fully sets in. Once it does it provides me with moderate pain relief and muscle relaxation.
Other than providing a great euphoria I find this strain is also a huge anxiety killer for me.
Over all I would definitely order this strain again. It's a shame this is a limited release from Tilray. The smell and taste alone make it worth keeping as a regular item. I enjoy having a good daytime indica that provides a sativa like euphoria.

Durban Poison is a Hell of a strain. It's fairly dense, looks and smells yummy and the smoke is smooth. It helps a lot with my GAD (General Anxiety Disorder) and it helps with my clinical depression, as well. It's a very uplifting high with a small indica buzz, you tingle slightly, but also feel very aware and focused. I've noticed it makes my friends and I giggle if we are not alone and we are smoking on this strain. I feel it would be good for people who have ADD/ADHD, Anxiety, and many other things that I have listed in the "Medical Condition" tab. Overall, I rate this strain a 4/5 stars.

Blue OG: for me, this was a vibrant and sharp ride of dualistic worlds where I would feel happy, light, creative mind's eye, and then if I relaxed into it, then I would feel it change like a light switch, flip, heavy-limbed, relaxed, and soft into the floor. Switching back and forth every 5-15 minutes for a great 2 hour trip. I would like to try this one with a giant blank canvas in front of me, lots of paint, and all walls covered in tarps because it would likely get messy.

An utter delight. A deep, pine green bud that warrants a double take. So humble at first, the richness of the hue is dark, and deep, but not dim. Almost glossy. Green suede, or a holly wreath.

The shade is curious, but the smell is where you really begin to understand. Lavender, lemon, and heady pine make a crisp perfume, far and away from any "skunky" or "sour" notes.

Nugs are hyperdense, being more akin to pebbles. Fairly crumbly once broken up, a smooth smoke that has an almost indulgent taste. A dandelion sugar cookie. 

Finishing on a triumphant crescendo, the high is nostalgic of your first time. Deep, ponderous, full bodied, a bit trippy if you over indulge.It embodies so well what being high is, taking a bit of the best traits, from some of the best strains, and merges into a complex buzz that manages to not feel muddled, or heavy.

For the experienced only, this strain will get even the jaded enthusiasts back into the spirit. While a surprisingly comfortable high,  it's probably best for low energy affairs. Nice dinners, or movie night. 

Best served with comfort food, your favorite album, and a warm hug.

I selected this strain from Private Label Organics in Southern Orange County.  This is a top shelf organic grow beautiful stuff, fluffy, yet still firm and yielding.  The buds are roundish and exhibit tons of orangish flame hairs and the whole bud has a light dusting of small crystals.  The buds in a bowl look to me like lichens or alpine mosses.  The effects are almost immediate.  The flavor is standard skunkish with a slight floral note, the relief it gives for even moderate to severe pain in amazing.  It still remains a functional strain.  I ground in my simba grinder, too my standard "scoop" which is about 1/4 gram and load it into my Vapor Tower, and pull through a KONG bong.  I am able to pull 4 decent sized hits, before tossing the "revape" into my collection jar for making canna-coconut oil.  The high remains in your head but the medicated effects really shine in the body with simple pain relief, and no overwhelming sluggishness or couch lock.  This is one that will stay in my medical cabinet as long as it's around.

I selected this strain from Choice in Southern Orange County.  This is a top shelf selection and my personal favorite INDICA of 2014. The effects are almost immediate, powerful and long lasting.  The flavor is insane, power pine-tree with heavy skunk funk and a woody foresty scent. This is not a functional strain.  I ground in my simba grinder, too my standard "scoop" which is about 1/4 gram and load it into my Vapor Tower, and pull through a KONG bong.  I am able to pull 5-6 decent sized hits, before tossing the "revape" into my collection jar for making canna-coconut oil.  The flavor is appreciated for minuets after you take a hit.  The effects are similar to and INDICA punch in the face.  You will sit down, and when you do the only reason you are getting up is to eat, and then maybe eat again.  Whatever was on your mind is no longer!  It makes me feel great, vapes like a dream.  The buds are firm and funky and caked up with white crystals.  Some red hairs poke through the buds and make them look like candle tips.   Whomever grew this batch knew WTF they were doing.  Best of 2014 in my books.

Overall pretty great, would try again but probably not for the price especially in this area.

Definitely look into Ice Cream if you're dealing with heavy pain on a day to day basis!

Skiing with the boys, we snuck off the trail and into the snowy trees where we planned to blaze a bowl. Still new to snowboarding, T-Baby ended up getting caught on an obstacle on the way down to the sesh, and dislocated his shoulder. Like a true toker, he fought off the pain, took his board off, and walked down the rest of the way to meet us. As we broke out the tropical buds, the guy with hair the same color of amber hairs on the crack dropped the lighter in the snow. Disheartened from the setback, we worked on getting the lighter to put out a flame for what seemed like an eternity. Finally, the purple lighter prevailed, and sent us to marijuana town. Focussed on the sport and giggly, we made our way down to the base and into the restaurant. With eyes redder than the C on the Colorado flag, we sat down at a table and starting laughing. Just as the curiosity of why there were so many children around us began to build, a ski instructor walked over to us and evicted us from our chilling spot, commenting on how it was reserved for ski school only. Maybe it was the Green Crack, but I couldn't help but feel like she subtly checked out my package as we left the table...

I just got Blue Dream, and it might be one of the best strains I've had so far. It's a hyrbid, but sativa-dominant and I can definitely tell. It doesn't make me pass out like most Indicas do, but I'm still capable of sleeping if tired (being high always encourages sleep for me).

I'm definitely happier, more hopeful, more stable post smoking than prior to smoking (had been lying in bed thinking of sadness). I smoked, then I was immediately thinking creative and more intelligent thoughts (evolutionary precursors of sex last night, and this morning about slightly more mystical information/origin of universe theories.  Still, that flow of creativity and interest is so much better than the miserable circles I get myself into. I feel energized, like someone came in and woke some other part of me up.

I now feel like I'm actually going to accomplish something with my day. Literally feel as though my depression is gone right now.

On the more simple side, flavor-wise I think it smells very woody, like a tree, like you've just stepped into a forest back home in Jersey, and also very sweet. Maybe like berries, but that might just be because I was conditioned to smell that. But definitely a sweet tree. It felt interesting, not very sticky but still... very non dry? I guess full of moisture without being sticky? But in a good way? Very nice weed to handle, basically.
I would recommend this specific strain to more advanced smokers who may be able to handle the many side effects of granddaddy purple.

The "Hit":  Tastes and hits great from both the bong or a vaporizer.  Gives even a seasoned smoker that "I gotta cough twinge".  On the insta-cough scale, I'd rate it a 7.5 or so.  5 minutes afterwards, the high will feel like a 8.5/10.

Appearance/Density:  Frosty white with crystals showing through a healthy emerald green bud underneath.  Almost looks white fuzzy moldy it's so covered in crystals (it's not actually moldy  ;) ).  Tightly packed, round/oval buds.  When ground up, it looks like it's about twice as much as you'd think it's so dense.

Flavor:  I'd describe as Pungent.  It's pleasant w/o being overwhelming.

Smell/Odor:  And with flavor comes smell/odor.  This strain is VEEEERY strong smelling.  There is no way you're opening the sealed container for this stuff indoors w/o it stinking up the whole place.  If you wanted a good representation of what medical MJ should smell like, this is it.  If you're walking around with it in your pocket, make sure it's in a sealed container of some sort, unless you're looking to attract a lot of attention.

Conclusion:  This strain is the perfect example of what a potent, healthy marijuana strain should be.  Dense nuggets that burn forever, and a powerful smell strong enough to make your eyes water, this is the definition of a overall outstanding strain.  Will be a repeat purchase for sure!

Bloody Voodoo is one of those hybrids that is a mix of sativa and indica from its Death Star, Voodoo, Northern Lights, Strawberry Cough and White Rhino it even known to have a mixture of other hybrids like Blue Dream, Red Dragon which is how it got the name voodoo. These plants will flower in 10-12 weeks and will produce whitish green flowers with traces of red. Its redness is evident in its pungent taste and smell, which has a musky quality tinged with strawberry sweetness. Since it was bred in the West, warm climates or indoors are best for growing (just be aware of the strong smell). As a good mix, this strain boasts both high THC and especially high CBD levels, making it a popular medicinal strain. The high also has a balanced feeling that is both clear and relaxing

Named after the Snoop Doggy Dogg track of the same name, tha shiznit is a medium to large sized plant with larger internodal spacing with chunky buds. Tha Shiznit has a thick stem and is main cola dominant with big fan leaves, long branches and round clustered buds. She is extremely extremely resinous and although these are generally frosty white in appearance, a percentage of plants will exhibit colour in the buds. This particular version of banana kush is exactly what even the most hard to please patient would expect of something carrying this name.

In terms of plant structure, the flowers are dense, high calyx count and short node spacing, with a brilliant green color showing through all the swollen reason glands. It's almost as nice to look at as it is to smoke.

The flavor is excellent. The spicy, earthy flavor on the exhale betrays the strain's haze roots, but the sweet fruitiness of the kush comes out more and more as it burns.

The high is mellow, and very relaxed, yet clear and happy. No problem eating, pain relief is strong and long lasting, and sleep is much easier.

Overall, I recommend this medicine to anyone who needs something strong, but can't be bogged down by heavy indica meds that rob them off clear thought and motivation. if I could give it six stars, I would.

This strain is perfect if you're looking for a very basic stoned feeling, though falling short of the super-blazed stoner movie stereotype type of stoned.  It's almost there, but missing some of the giddiness and spontaneous bursts of laughter.  This isn't necessarily a bad thing, since it's way easier to keep a straight face or play serious if the need arises.  The head feels like it's stuffed with cotton and there's a sense of attempted - but not quite there - mental clarity. It's almost like bringing your toolbox to deal with a big project you're familiar with and not being able to find all the tools needed: the intent and focus are there, but the facilities to make use of these is lacking.  

Not bad for, say, writing internet reviews or reading some straightforward comics.  Video games that require a bit of mental processing power or reading/watching something with a complex plot are a bit out of reach, but dumb comedies or big loud explosions are great!

A balanced strain that veers slightly more towards a characteristic indica while retaining the focus, social and functional high of it's sativa parent. White Widow is a smooth smoke and vape with no harshness whatsoever. Not a cerebral strain as it doesn't have you daydreaming or thinking too deeply; meaning that taking too much does not lead to paranoia or racing thoughts. Look elsewhere for more "specific" highs as White Widow is not the best indica nor the best sativa, but rather a very good combination of both. White Widow is for indica lovers who don't want to be put to sleep and for sativa lovers who don't want their minds racing. The strain induces fairly strong munchies and also has fluffy buds that grind very well; great for joint rolling. Overall White Widow a very solid hybrid  that is sure to have something for everyone.

Sour diesel- I smoked this strain today, and it was really good. Even before I smoked it I could tell this was going to be an excellent high. I smoked a small amount, and my high was very much like my experience on Adderall. I was able to focus very well on one particular thing, while simultaneously ignoring any distractions easily. Everything besides what you are focusing on just goes in the background which would allow me to focus. I later smoked this strain again and then played basketball. My hand eye coordination was a little lacking compared to how it is on some other strains. Not for normal activities, but I noticed this when I played basketball while high, and this is not the case with all strains. Sometimes my hand eye coordination is excellent after I smoke. Sometimes after smoking, I feel as if the basketball and my hand are one, allowing me to handle the ball with precision and creativity. However, it wasn’t bad, and I still was able to play well. I could definitely see myself smoking this during the day and getting shit done. After basketball I went home, smoked some more, and went to sleep. My sleep was excellent, which is normally not the case. Not sure if it was the basketball or the weed. I think it was a little of both.

Oh yea, it’s also a good social strain. I was more talkative on the basketball court and communicating effectively. I attribute this to the bud, because I normally don’t talk as much on the court.

Acquired medically from Planet Joe at the NW Cannabis Market. Space Bomb has an incredibly complex flavor and aroma, like few others. Sweet, and earthy notes of pine, sage, a sweet floral flavor I can't quite describe specifically. The many layered flavor is definitely to be savored. The effect comes on gently, but definite. Living up to its name and parentage, your head is lifted to a floaty, ebbing and flowing peaceful happiness. Even heavy worries fade a bit, as the heavy, tingling body feel takes over. Pain melts, and eases away replaced by a wonderful euphoria to match the peaceful mental state. Sense of touch is amplified making that hot shower feel incredible, and be that much more effective at relaxing the mind and body. A great overall effect, happy, creative mind with substantial physical relief and pleasure. Great at improving appetite. Be calm, and happy, feel good throughout your day, as Space Bomb allows one to still be active, if a bit daydreamy. Recommend it for everyone, couples will love it.

[I just recovered from depression after 10 years of different treatments, finally working with a doctor who continuously monitors me so that I don't need to be on meds and see psychiatrists ever again. I still have insomnia, but my doctor thinks that will neutralize itself once my brain is fully healed.] 
My brain is by default hyperactive, so with Pineapple Kush, it puts it into overdrive and I am more easily triggered to get into intense conversations, debates, and/or rants, which then tenses me up and raises my blood pressure. 

Could be safe for you, maybe, if you are feeling a mental block and want something to ignite a fire in there... just be wary about potentially combusting, metaphorically speaking.

I recently came to really enjoy using marijuana.   I tried for a long time to like it and just flat out did not enjoy it.  it made me paranoid and stressed out.  I was doing a little research on the different strains out there and started to understand more about what marijuana really is.  I then realized that I was getting mostly thc dominant strains and how that was having an effect on my enjoyment or lack there of.  I came across an edible that was called Sugar Cookie.  I took it home, popped one into my mouth and waited....  Mentally, I had prepared myself for another anxiety ridden and paranoia filled next few hours.  To my consternation and surprise I suddenly realized how smooth, relaxed and nice I was feeling!  I was incredibly excited because my blood pressure dropped, anxiety disappeared and confidence came rushing back to me in a very tangible way.  I was not feeling super "high" but just completely at ease and ok with the world.  Its amazing how much sugar cookie has done for me and I truly wish it was more readily available.

This is a guaranteed hall of famer in the cannabis industry. I have friends who literally HATE indicas and won't smoke 1 for any reason at all, but if they can get their hands on sum GDP then all of a sudden they're bandwagon jumpers (until they run out of their GDP stash). This is also a GREAT purple indica to grow outdoors as it produces a larger yield than most indicas (especially PURPLE indicas). I've grown purple urkle by itself in a 10 gallon pot which I didn't even plant til late June which sucks cuz I woulda yielded alot more had I planted it in early March which is what I do now, so this urkle was just a baby when I got it and on top of that,I didn't even bother buying high nitrogen plant food for a month or so until I realized that it wasn't growing hardly at all. So I went and bought sum fox farm "grow big" 6-4-4. I started using that in late July and damn near immediately the plant started getting very bushy like indicas always do, the stock started growing thick and so did the branches and the height even started taking off. Come harvest time it was November 14th and it was supposed to rain the next day, so I had been flushing the plant for 8 days with just clean,plain water. And to make the buds look magical, since Halloween it had been getting down into the low 50's at night, so every night before bed I would go to the grocery store and buy a bag full of ice and then dump the ice all over the soil and around the plant. This worked perfect as I was able to get it just cold enough every night so it made my buds a beautiful purple color like I had never seen before. I also experimented a lil too and when I would flush the plant out with clean water and molasses to make the buds super sticky. I would also put kool aid (grape flavor) and OMG this increased the berry smell and grape taste. This was sum grade A bud. The high was equally as good if not better than the stuff (including other purple urkle batches at dispensaries). I got my grow to look more purple and it had a better high! But unfortunately due to the fact that I didn't plant it until too late in the growing season and I also didn't get good/high nitrogen plant food so I was lucky to harvest the lil 2 ounces I got on that grow. I want some GDP seeds to grow and plant in early March to get it huge and I'd be curious to see how much bigger of a yield that GDP would get me compared to other purple indicas

The Sativa dominant strain Cabbage Patch was recommended to me by one of OrganiCann's budtenders as a strain that they could, "smoke all day, with a minimal comedown." I found this to be true along with the other patients I shared the strain with. 

Cabbage Patch looks and smells totally sweet. It has a platinum coating of crystals and is fluffy with a light texture of red hairs. It smells of lavender and honey, and the greens hit tastes of clean sage and violet. 

The high is a smooth elevation into an energetic, happy, creative, and conversational state, while lacking a hard, heady edge. It's percentage of indica is low, but it's just the right amount for balancing it's strong sativa characteristics. It can get buzzy at higher levels of consumption, but the indica keeps the sativa high at bay, adding a warm and grounding feel to an otherwise pure energy high. Overall, the effects of this balance are very good. 

The Cabbage Patch high allows for collaborative efforts between people, and a presence that is often strong and lucid. I found myself listening intently to others without spacing out and communicating clearly with a cutting perspective. I felt motivated to shape the world around me, while paying attention to the world and what it had to say. 

When the high fades, it's mainly a return to a normal state. It generally fades after a couple hours if you're smoking it. People I've shared the herb with often comment on how much energy they have after the comedown. There's a very slight fog, but it's not distracting or debilitating. Using Cabbage Patch throughout the day works well, as the budtender suggested, and overall it's exactly what I'm looking from a sativa dominant strain.

Make no mistake, CBD dominant strains ARE psychoactive.  You may or may not like the high, but if you inhale enough (more than one hit) there is a high.  I experience highs like notes in a symphony; a constant buzz of low, middle and high notes.  Harle-Tsu is all the violins in an orchestra playing their highest screeching notes at the same time.  As advertised, Harle-Tsu is good (excellent) for pain, but the nature of the mental high isn't enjoyable enough for me to want to use it.  I have vaped isopropyl extracted oil in a cartridge pen (dàmà) made from the CBD dominant ACDC strain, and it was a much more mellower, pleasant, and not even remotely annoying experience.  I do look forward to mixing some of this Harle with the dankest indica I can get my hands on.  That might be interesting.

Smoked a joint of WW a few months ago. It was much stronger than I had predicted. I ended up eating an insane amount of food. Then, I began to watch videos on YouTube on weird space phenomena, and the workings of the universe. I began to get very paranoid and delusional. I started to think my heart was beating too fast, and that it was unable to downshift to the next gear. I feared it was never going to calm down. I started to develop heart palpitations as my anxiety grew. I ended up seeing 2 cardiologists, as the heart palpitations never stopped after sobering up. I took a very long break from smoking and consuming caffeine, and waited for the answer from the doctor's as to what was wrong with my heart. Eventually the conclusion was that my heart was creating these symptoms from stress. This whole time, it was all anxiety about having a heart condition that ended up giving me a heart condition. Albeit still prevalent, the palpitations have since relaxed in frequency and intenseness, and I am proud to be smoking weed once again.

Cactus is one of those strains that you simply do not forget. A deeply rooted earthy aroma complemented by complex floral fragrances that emanate from this juicy bud's core may be the first thing you notice about this beautiful flower. It's pungent, nostril scrunching capabilities are sure to baffle and amaze any who come into its presence. Diamond-sapphire crystals burst from every crevasse and bright orange hairs reach out in all directions. The stone is equally complex and while it is a potent indica, it feigns a super sativa, making for very spacey, psychedelic moments in between bouts of intense chillage and relaxation. Of all the strains I have tried, this one in particular carried the scent over to the flavor of the smoke, making it almost sweet. I simply can't say enough about this strain. It's amazing! A favorite for sure.

Like many other reviewers here, I also suffer from PTSD (10 years of the domestic variety).  Like other PTSD folks, I have good days and bad days.  The past two months have been especially difficult as I'm going through a rough period in my life.  I tried Headband for the first time a couple of nights ago.  I am temporarily on a bong until my vaporizer arrives in the mail.  Not all strains work well with PTSD (some can actually make symptoms worse).  Headband IS a strain that works exceedingly well for me.  After 2 or 3 good tokes, the delusional paranoid thinking and severe depression subsided.  Another common symptom of PTSD is digestive problems.  My weight dropped from 105lbs to 94lbs between late November to present due to lack of appetite from spastic colon (horribly painful) and nausea.  Headband immediately alleviated all spasms within five minutes after use, which makes it an excellent pain reliever as well.  I was finally able to eat a decent amount of food yesterday without doubling over in pain, and feel much better today because of it.  I also found Headband helps with fatigue.  I was relaxed and mellow without being couch locked, making it a good choice for daytime use.  Headband wouldn't be my first recommendation for wanting to get super high.  It does make you high, but not blasted.  You will feel buzzed, but won't be seeing pink bunnies shooting paintballs at you anytime soon.  Highly recommend!

The body effects were very soothing, relaxing like having two beers, but with a very clear head similar to how you feel after a long run or hard workout.

I would definitely recommend having this strain in your stash.

Jason King wrote about Herijuana back in 2001 in the Cannabible and said "most people simply shouldn't smoke it", which I took as a challange. 14 years on the east coast and never came across it, this being my holy grail strain. I moved to Colorado this year and immediately pursued this, my most sought after of nugs. My room mate works for a dispensery and they had Orange Herijuana, of which I was very unimpressed. Beautiful nugs and amazing smell but the sativa cross was counter productive to what I had hoped and anticipated Herijuanas high to be. needless to say I was saddened. Had my expectations been too high? Did I just hype a small paragraph on a strain in a book written almost 15 years ago? My room mates who have lived in Colorado for years hadn't had Herijuana and u felt determined to show them, and more importantly myself, Herijuana was the strongest nug available. At least strongest as far as I've rated a high, being from the NY/NJ area. Finally tracing down and grabbing that first gram of pure Herijuana was as exciting as it was nerve racking! Will it be what I believed it to be all this time or would I be let down again like I was with her sweet and unique orange cousin? I had been dabbing heavily the 2 weeks leading to the aquisition of the Herijuana so that added to the odds stacked against her. also was the multitude of other amazing and beautiful nugs in town like the Pacific Coast Kush I got that smelled and tasted like heaven or my room mates favorite golden goat which still tastes like a dream u once had as a kid. The bong rips of Herijuana(2 rips) were almost instant affirmation of all my years of wondering. This shit is without a doubt the most bad ass pot I ever had! I barely made it to the couch before re discovering hot rod on Netflix and feeling accomplished in life in a way I never had before. I moved to Colorado from the east coast to pursue a career in the industry and to have my extract making room mates applaud the high Herijuana gave them after seeking it exclusively for SO long was a way I've felt proves to me I knew what I was talking about when I read the only bible that ever meant anything to me. Thanks Mr. King, that shit was totally worth the wait.

could hear EVERYTHING. the cars driving down the street sounding intensely amazing. even after the real buzz calmed down ( I wouldn't call it mellow--i wish the funny stage lasted a lot longer) I pull out the chapstick from my pocket thinking it was the pipe and held it up to light up before i saw what i was holding lol. couldn't keep track of everything in my pockets as i had bags of buds and a pipe and a lighter and visine and a knife and everything else i carry everytime i tried to get something out of my pockets. it was funny as hell, but hell isn't funny that's serious shit. don't
